<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-12pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:12pt; font-size:12pt; color:#000000">Item 8.01.</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:72pt; line-height:12pt; font-size:12pt; color:#000000"><U>Other Events</U>.</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:12pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:12pt; font-size:12pt; color:#000000"><U>Filing of Computational Materials</U></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:12pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:36pt; line-height:12pt; font-size:12pt; color:#000000">Pursuant to Rule 424(b) under the Securities Act of 1933, concurrently with, or subsequent to, the filing of this Current Report on Form 8-K (the &#147;Form 8-K&#148;), Asset Backed Securities Corporation (the &#147;Company&#148;) is filing a prospectus and prospectus supplement with the Securities and Exchange Commission relating to its Asset Backed Securities Corporation Home Equity Loan Trust 2005-HE1, Asset Backed Pass-Through Certificates, Series 2005-HE1.</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:12pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:36pt; line-height:12pt; font-size:12pt; color:#000000">In connection with the offering of the Asset Backed Securities Corporation Home Equity Loan Trust 2005-HE1 Asset Backed Pass-Through Certificates, Series 2005-HE1, Credit Suisse First Boston LLC (&#147;CSFB&#148;), as one of the underwriters of the Certificates, has prepared certain materials (the &#147;Computational Materials&#148;) for distribution to their potential investors. &nbsp;Although the Company provided CSFB with certain information regarding the characteristics of the mortgage loans in the related portfolio, the Company did not participate in the preparation of the Computational Materials.</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:12pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:36pt; line-height:12pt; font-size:12pt; color:#000000">The Computational Materials are attached hereto as Exhibit 99.1.</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:12pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:12pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<BR>

<BR>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:8pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>

<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:12pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>

<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-8pt; padding-left:36pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-36pt; line-height:8pt; font-size:8pt; color:#000000">(2)</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:36pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:8pt; font-size:8pt; color:#000000">To 10% optional clean-up call at the Pricing Speed, in months.</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-8pt; padding-left:36pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-36pt; line-height:8pt; font-size:8pt; color:#000000">(3)</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:36pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:8pt; font-size:8pt; color:#000000">The Certificates will accrue interest at a rate based on LIBOR plus a margin, subject to the related Available Funds Cap. &nbsp;The margin on the Class A Certificates will double, the margin on the Class M Certificates will increase 1.5x after the first Distribution Date on which the optional clean-up call is exercisable. &nbsp;</P>

</TD></TR>

<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=center><BR></P>
<TABLE style="margin-left:0pt"><TR><BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=right><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:8pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:8pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<HR style="padding-top:7.2pt; padding-bottom:7.2pt; color:#000000" noshade size=1.333>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:7pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:0pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:-34.25pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:14pt; color:#000000" align=right><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:14pt; font-size:14pt; color:#000000"><B>ASSET BACKED SECURITIES CORPORATION</B></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:11pt; font-size:11pt; color:#000000"><B>HOME EQUITY LOAN TRUST, SERIES 2005-HE1</B></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:-29.75pt; padding-bottom:3pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:7.5pt; font-size:7.5pt; color:#000000; border-bottom:3pt solid #000000">This page must be accompanied by a disclaimer. If you did not receive such a disclaimer, please contact Credit Suisse First Boston LLC.</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:11pt; color:#000000" align=right><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:3.5pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:7pt; color:#000000" align=right><BR></P>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=156.533><P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:5pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:5pt; padding-left:3.6pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:3.6pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><B>Principal Distributions:</B></P>
</TD><TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=516><P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:3.6pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:3.6pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">Collections of principal before the Stepdown Date, or if a Trigger Event exists, will be allocated in the following priority:</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:54pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-18pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">1.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:54pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">&nbsp;Pay the Class A Certificates to zero. The Class A1 Certificates and the Class A2 Certificates will be paid the Group I Percentage of the total principal remittance amount, pro rata, until their balance has been reduced to zero; provided however, that on any Distribution Date on or after which the Subordinate Certificates have been reduced to zero and the Excess Interest and Overcollateralization Amounts for such Distribution Date are insufficient to cover Realized Losses on the Group I Mortgage Loans, sequentially to the Class A1 Certificates and Class A2 Certificates, in that order, until their balance has been reduced to zero. &nbsp;The Class A3 Certificates will be paid its pro rata portion of the Group II Percentage of the total principal remittance amount until such class principal balance has been reduced to zero. &nbsp;The Class A4 Cer
tificates will be paid the pro rata portion of the Group II Percentage of the total principal remittance amount allocable to the Class A4 Certificates, Class A5 Certificates and Class A6 Certificates until its class principal balance has been reduced to zero, then the Class A5 Certificates will be paid the pro rata portion of the Group II Percentage of the total principal remittance amount allocable to the Class A5 Certificates and Class A6 Certificates until its class principal balance has been reduced to zero and then the Class A6 Certificates will be paid its pro rata portion of the Group II Percentage until its class principal balance has been reduced to zero. &nbsp;After the class principal balance of either group of Class A Certificates has been reduced to zero, any remaining amounts will be distributed to the other group, if outstanding.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:54pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-18pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">2.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:54pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">Pay the principal remittance amount to the Class M1, Class M2, Class M3, Class M4, Class M5, Class M6, Class M7, Class M8, Class M9, Class M10 and Class M11 Certificates sequentially to zero.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:3.6pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:3.6pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">Collections of principal on and after the Stepdown Date, and if a Trigger Event does not exist, will be allocated in the following priority:</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:54pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-18pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">1.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:54pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">Pay the Class A Certificates to their target enhancement level (the &#147;Class A Principal Distribution Amount&#148;). &nbsp;The Class A1 Certificates and the Class A2 Certificates will be paid to the Group I Percentage of the Class A Principal Distribution Amount, pro rata; provided however, that on any Distribution Date on or after which the Subordinate Certificates have been reduced to zero and the Excess Interest and Overcollateralization Amounts for such Distribution Date are insufficient to cover Realized Losses on the Group I Mortgage Loans sequentially to the Class A1 Certificates and Class A2 Certificates, in that order, until their balance has been reduced to zero. &nbsp;&nbsp;The Class A3 Certificates will be paid its pro rata portion of the Group II Percentage of the Class A Principal Distribution Amount until such class principal bala
nce has been reduced to zero. &nbsp;The Class A4 Certificates will be paid the pro rata portion of the Group II Percentage of the Class A Principal Distribution Amount allocable to the Class A4 Certificates, Class A5 Certificates and Class A6 Certificates until its class principal balance has been reduced to zero, then the Class A5 Certificates will be paid the pro rata portion of the Group II Percentage of the Class A Principal Distribution Amount allocable to the Class A5 Certificates and Class A6 Certificates until its class principal balance has been reduced to zero and the Class A6 Certificates will be paid its pro rata portion of the Group II Percentage of the Class A Principal Distribution Amount until its class principal balance has been reduced to zero. &nbsp;</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:54pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-18pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">2.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:54pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">Pay the Class M1 Certificates to their targeted enhancement level.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:54pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-18pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">3.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:54pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">Pay the Class M2 Certificates to their targeted enhancement level.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:54pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-18pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">4.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:54pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">Pay the Class M3 Certificates to their targeted enhancement level.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:54pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-18pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">5.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:54pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">Pay the Class M4 Certificates to their targeted enhancement level.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:54pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-18pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">6.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:54pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">Pay the Class M5 Certificates to their targeted enhancement level.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:54pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-18pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">7.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:54pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">Pay the Class M6 Certificates to their targeted enhancement level.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:54pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-18pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">8.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:54pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">Pay the Class M7 Certificates to their targeted enhancement level.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:54pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-18pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">9.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:54pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">Pay the Class M8 Certificates to their targeted enhancement level.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:54pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-18pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">10.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:54pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">Pay the Class M9 Certificates to their targeted enhancement level.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:54pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-18pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">11.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:54pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">Pay the Class M10 Certificates to their targeted enhancement level.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:54pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-18pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">12.</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:5pt; padding-left:54pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">Pay the Class M11 Certificates to their targeted enhancement level.</P>
</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=center><BR></P>
<TABLE style="margin-left:0pt"><TR><TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=156.533><P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:5pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:5pt; padding-left:3.6pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:3.6pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><B>Class A2 Certificates:</B></P>
</TD><TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=517.333 colspan=3><P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:5pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:5pt; padding-left:3.6pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:3.6pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">The Class A2 Certificates will receive principal payments pro rata with Class A1 Certificates but will act as a first loss certificate. &nbsp;In the event that losses reach the Class A Certificates, the losses allocated to the Group I Certificates will be absorbed first by the Class A2 Certificates and then the Class A1 Certificates. &nbsp;</P>
</TD></TR>
<TR><TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=156.533><P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:5pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:5pt; padding-left:3.6pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:3.6pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><B>Group I Percentage:</B></P>
</TD><TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=517.333 colspan=3><P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:5pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:5pt; padding-left:3.6pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:3.6pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">The principal remittance amount for the Group I Collateral divided by the principal remittance amount for the total collateral.</P>
</TD></TR>
<TR><TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=156.533><P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:5pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:5pt; padding-left:3.6pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:3.6pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><B>Group II Percentage:</B></P>
</TD><TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=517.333 colspan=3><P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:5pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:5pt; padding-left:3.6pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:3.6pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">The principal remittance amount for the Group II Collateral divided by the principal remittance amount for the total collateral.</P>
</TD></TR>
<TR><TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=157.867 colspan=2><P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:5pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:5pt; padding-left:3.6pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:3.6pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><B>Overcollateralization Provisions:</B></P>
</TD><TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=516 colspan=2><P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:3.6pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:3.6pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">Any Net Monthly Excess Cashflow will be paid as follows:</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:54pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:3.6pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-18pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">1.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:54pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:3.6pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">To the Certificates in an amount equal to the principal portion of any realized losses on the mortgage loans.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:54pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:3.6pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-18pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">2.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:54pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:3.6pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">To the Certificates to build the Overcollateralization Amount to the target level.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:54pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:3.6pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-18pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">3.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:54pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:3.6pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">Unpaid Interest Shortfalls and Unpaid Realized Losses, in that order, sequentially to the Class M1 Certificates, Class M2 Certificates, Class M3 Certificates, Class M4 Certificates, Class M5 Certificates, Class M6 Certificates, Class M7 Certificates, Class M8 Certificates, Class M9 Certificates, Class M10 Certificates and Class M11 Certificates, in that order.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:54pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:3.6pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-18pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">4.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:54pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:3.6pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">Reimbursement for prepayment interest shortfalls, first pari-passu to the Class A1, Class A2, Class A3, Class A4, Class A5 and Class A6 Certificates, then sequentially to the Class M1 Certificates, Class M2 Certificates, Class M3 Certificates, Class M4 Certificates, Class M5 Certificates, Class M6 Certificates, Class M7 Certificates, Class M8 Certificates, Class M9 Certificates, Class M10 Certificates and Class M11 Certificates, in that order.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:5pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:-10pt; padding-left:54pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:3.6pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-18pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">5.</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:5pt; padding-left:54pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:3.6pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">Carry Forward Amount first pari-passu to the Class A1, Class A2, Class A3, Class A4, Class A5 and Class A6 Certificates, and then sequentially to the Class M1 Certificates, Class M2 Certificates, Class M3 Certificates, Class M4 Certificates, Class M5 Certificates, Class M6 Certificates, Class M7 Certificates, Class M8 Certificates, Class M9 Certificates, Class M10 Certificates and the Class M11 Certificates, in that order.</P>
</TD></TR>
<TR><BR>

<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=right><BR></P>

<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:11pt; font-size:11pt; color:#000000"><B>HOME EQUITY LOAN TRUST, SERIES 2005-HE1</B></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:-29.75pt; padding-bottom:3pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:7.5pt; font-size:7.5pt; color:#000000; border-bottom:3pt solid #000000">This page must be accompanied by a disclaimer. If you did not receive such a disclaimer, please contact Credit Suisse First Boston LLC.</P>

<BR>
<BR>
<TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=157.867 colspan=2><P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:5pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:5pt; padding-left:3.6pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:3.6pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><B>Group I Net WAC Rate</B></P>
</TD><TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=516 colspan=2><P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:5pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:5pt; padding-left:3.6pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:3.6pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">The Group I weighted average mortgage rate less the sum of the Servicing Fee rate.</P>
</TD></TR>
<TR><TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=157.867 colspan=2><P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:5pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:5pt; padding-left:3.6pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:3.6pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><B>Group II Net WAC Rate</B></P>
</TD><TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=516 colspan=2><P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:5pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:5pt; padding-left:3.6pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:3.6pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">The Group II weighted average mortgage rate less the sum of the Servicing Fee rate.</P>
</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=center><BR></P>
<TABLE style="margin-left:0pt"><TR><TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=157.867 colspan=2><P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:5pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:5pt; padding-left:3.6pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:3.6pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><B>Available Funds Cap:</B></P>
</TD><TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=516 colspan=2><P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:3.6pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:3.6pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">The Class A Certificates will generally be subject to their related Available Funds Cap equal to their related group Net WAC Rate less (expressed as a percentage of their groups respective outstanding collateral balance) the related Cap Fee rate. </P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:5pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:5pt; padding-left:3.6pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:3.6pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">The Class M Certificates will generally be subject to their related Available Funds Cap equal to (a) the weighted average (weighted in proportion to the results of subtracting from the aggregate principal balance of each loan group the current principal balance of the related Class A Certificates), of the Available Funds Cap for each of Group I and Group II less the related Cap Fee rate (expressed as a percentage of the aggregate principal balance of the Mortgage Loans less the current principal balance of the Class A Certificates).</P>
</TD></TR>
<TR><TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=157.867 colspan=2><P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:5pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:5pt; padding-left:3.6pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:3.6pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><B>Available Funds Cap Carry Forward:</B></P>
</TD><TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=516 colspan=2><P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:5pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:5pt; padding-left:3.6pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:3.6pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">If interest collections on a Distribution Date are insufficient to make required interest payments to a class of Certificates due to the related Available Funds Cap, amounts unpaid to such class of Certificates will be carried forward to the next Distribution Date (the &#147;Carry Forward Amount&#148;). &nbsp;Carry Forward Amounts at the next Distribution Date will include interest on the Carry Forward Amount, calculated at the applicable Certificate Rate. &nbsp;</P>
</TD></TR>
<TR><TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=156.533><P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:5pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:5pt; padding-left:3.6pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:3.6pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><B>Overcollateralization:</B></P>
</TD><TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=517.333 colspan=3><P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:3.6pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:3.6pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">Overcollateralization will be fully-funded at [2.90%] of the aggregate original principal balance of the mortgage loans, stepping down on the Stepdown Date, provided a Trigger Event is not in effect, to [5.80%] of the aggregate outstanding principal balance of the mortgage loans, subject to the Overcollateralization Floor. &nbsp;If a Trigger Event is in effect, the Overcollateralization Target Amount will equal the Target Amount for the immediately preceding period.</P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:5pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:5pt; padding-left:3.6pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:3.6pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">Overcollateralization Floor: 0.50% of the aggregate principal balance of the mortgage loans as of the Cut-Off Date.</P>
</TD></TR>
<TR><TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=156.533><P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:5pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:5pt; padding-left:3.6pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:3.6pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><B>Stepdown Date:</B></P>
</TD><TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=517.333 colspan=3><P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:5pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:5pt; padding-left:3.6pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:3.6pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">The earlier of (i) the Distribution Date on which the aggregate certificate principal balance of the Class A Certificates has been reduced to zero, and (ii) the later to occur of (x) the Distribution Date in [March 2008] and (y) the first Distribution Date on which the Credit Enhancement Percentage is greater than or equal to [40.00%].</P>
</TD></TR>
<TR><TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=156.533><P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><B>Credit Enhancement:</B></P>
</TD><TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=517.333 colspan=3>&nbsp;</TD></TR>
</TABLE>

<TABLE style="margin-left:0pt"><TR><TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=156.533><P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:5pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:5pt; padding-left:3.6pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:3.6pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><B>Coupon Step-Ups:</B></P>
</TD><TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=516><P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:5pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:5pt; padding-left:3.6pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:3.6pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">On the Distribution Date after the earliest date on which the optional clean up call can be exercised, the margin on the Class A Certificates will double and the margin on the Class M Certificates will increase by 1.5x.</P>
</TD></TR>

<TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=156.533><P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:5pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:5pt; padding-left:3.6pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:3.6pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><B>Cap Contract:</B></P>
</TD><TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=516><P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:5pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:5pt; padding-left:3.6pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:3.6pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">The Trust will include Cap Contracts for the benefit of the Group I Certificates, Group II Certificates and Class M Certificates. &nbsp;The notional balance, strike and ceiling rate of each Cap Contract for any Distribution Date will be based on the applicable amount specified in the charts on Pages 11 through 13. &nbsp;In exchange for a monthly fee (&#147;Cap Fee&#148;), the counterparty will be obligated to make monthly payments to the Trust when one-month LIBOR is equal to, or exceeds the strike rate beginning with the Distribution Date in April 2005. &nbsp;Such payments will be capped at their maximum amount when one-month LIBOR equals or exceeds the ceiling ra
te. &nbsp;The Group I Certificates Cap Contract, the Group II Certificates Cap Contract and the Class M Certificates Cap Contract will terminate after the Distribution Date in June 2008.</P>
</TD></TR>
<TR><TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=156.533><P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:3.6pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:3.6pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><B>Trigger Event:</B></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
</TD><TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=516><P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">A Trigger Event is in effect on any Distribution Date on or after the Stepdown Date, if either (i) the percentage of mortgage loans greater than 60 days or more delinquent exceeds [38%] of the Credit Enhancement Percentage or (ii) the cumulative realized losses as a percentage of the mortgage loans, as of the Cut-off Date are greater than:</P>
</TD></TR>

<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>

</TD><TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=187.733><P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:144pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-144pt; line-height:9pt; font-size:9pt; color:#000000" align=center><B>Percentage</B></P>
</TD></TR>

<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:36pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:7pt; font-size:7pt; color:#000000" align=justify>Assumes the pricing speed.</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-7pt; padding-left:36pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-18pt; line-height:7pt; font-size:7pt; color:#000000" align=justify>(2)</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:36pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:7pt; font-size:7pt; color:#000000" align=justify>Calculated as (a) interest collections on the collateral (net of the Servicing Fee and Cap Fees), less total interest on the Certificates divided by (b) collateral balance as of the beginning period, times twelve.</P>

<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:-7pt; padding-left:36pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:-18pt; line-height:7pt; font-size:7pt; color:#000000" align=justify>(1)</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:36pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:7pt; font-size:7pt; color:#000000" align=justify>Assumes 1 month and 6 month LIBOR instantaneously increases to a level beyond the highest maximum obtainable rate on the adjustable rate mortgage loans and is run at the Pricing Speed and includes all cash proceeds from the related Cap. Assumes 1 month and 6 month LIBOR equal 20%. </P>

<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:36pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:7pt; font-size:7pt; color:#000000" align=justify>Assumes 1 month and 6 month LIBOR instantaneously increases to a level beyond the highest maximum obtainable rate on the adjustable rate mortgage loans and is run at the Pricing Speed and includes all cash proceeds from the related Cap. Assumes 1 month and 6 month LIBOR equal 20%. </P>

<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:14pt; font-size:14pt; color:#000000"><B>ASSET BACKED SECURITIES CORPORATION</B></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:11pt; font-size:11pt; color:#000000"><B>HOME EQUITY LOAN TRUST, SERIES 2005-HE1</B></P>
<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:-29.75pt; padding-bottom:3pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:7.5pt; font-size:7.5pt; color:#000000; border-bottom:3pt solid #000000">This page must be accompanied by a disclaimer. <BR>
<BR>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:14pt; font-size:14pt; color:#000000" align=center><B>BREAKEVEN CDR TABLE</B></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:9pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">The tables below display the Constant Default Rate (&#147;CDR&#148;), and the related cumulative collateral loss, where the referenced Class first incurs a writedown. Calculations are run to maturity at both static and forward LIBOR. Other assumptions incorporated include: </P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:9pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:27pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">(1) prepayment speed is 115% PPC for Fixed Rate Mortgages and</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:9pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:99pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;100% PPC for Adjustable Rate Mortgages, </P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:9pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:27pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">(2) 40% loss severity, </P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:9pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:27pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">(3) 12 month lag from default to loss, and </P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left:9pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom:0pt; text-indent:27pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">(4) triggers fail (i.e., no stepdown). </P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<TABLE style="margin-left:0pt"><TR><TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=120 rowspan=2><P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
</TD><TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=170.8 colspan=2><P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:8pt; font-size:8pt; color:#000000" align=center><B>Static LIBOR</B></P>
</TD><TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=165.2 colspan=2><P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:8pt; font-size:8pt; color:#000000" align=center><B>Forward LIBOR</B></P>
</TD></TR>
<TR><TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=96><P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:8pt; font-size:8pt; color:#000000" align=center><B>CDR Break (%)</B></P>
</TD><TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=74.8><P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:8pt; font-size:8pt; color:#000000" align=center><B>Cum Loss</B></P>
</TD><TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=93.2><P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:8pt; font-size:8pt; color:#000000" align=center><B>CDR Break (%)</B></P>
</TD><TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=72><P style="margin:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:8pt; font-size:8pt; color:#000000" align=center><B>Cum Loss</B></P>
</TD></TR>

<P style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:-29.75pt; padding-bottom:3pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:7.5pt; font-size:7.5pt; color:#000000; border-bottom:3pt solid #000000">This page must be accompanied by a disclaimer. <P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:9pt; font-size:9pt; color:#000000" align=center><B>MORTGAGE LOANS</B></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><B>The Mortgage Loans primarily consist of first lien 2/28 and 3/27 adjustable rate loans, first lien and second lien fixed rate closed-end home equity loans, and interest-only loans. &nbsp;The 2/28 and 3/27 adjustable rate loans are primarily subject to semi-annual interest rate adjustments after an initial twenty-four or thirty-six month period, respectively. &nbsp;The obligations of the Borrower under each mortgage are secured by the related property.</B></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>

<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:14pt; font-size:14pt; color:#000000" align=center>Five sets of tables follow. &nbsp;</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:14pt; font-size:14pt; color:#000000">The first set of tables is the Total Pool Collateral.</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:14pt; font-size:14pt; color:#000000">The second set of tables is the New Century Collateral.</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:14pt; font-size:14pt; color:#000000">The third set of tables is the WMC Collateral.</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:14pt; font-size:14pt; color:#000000">The fourth set of tables is the Group I Pool which consist of Conforming Collateral that conforms with Fannie Mae or Freddie Mac Guidelines.</P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:14pt; font-size:14pt; color:#000000">The fifth set of tables is the Group II Pool which consists of collateral that may or may not conform to Fannie Mae or Freddie Mac Guidelines.</P>

<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<TABLE style="margin-left:0pt"><TR><TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=103.2><P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:2pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:8pt; font-size:8pt; color:#000000"><B>Occupancy Status</B></P>

<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:10pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000" align=center><B>ORIGINAL TERM TO EXPIRATION OF PREPAYMENT PENALTY</B></P>
<P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size:10pt; color:#000000"><BR></P>
<TABLE style="margin-left:0pt"><TR><TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=107.867><P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:2pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:8pt; font-size:8pt; color:#000000"><B>Original Number of Months to Expiration</B></P>
</TD><TD style="padding-left:1.2pt; padding-top:0pt; padding-right:1.2pt; padding-bottom:0pt" align=left valign=top width=60.933><P style="margin-left:0pt; margin-top:2pt; margin-right:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; padding:0pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:8pt; font-size:8pt; color:#000000" align=center><B>Number of Loans</B></P>
